SIMPLE: heddle
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Heddle
<hw>Hed"dle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Heddles</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Cf. <er>Heald</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Weaving)</fld> <def>One of the sets of parallel doubled threads
which, with mounting, compose the harness employed to guide the warp
threads to the lathe or batten in a loom.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heddle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Heddle
<hw>Hed"dle</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To draw (the warp thread)
through the heddle-eyes, in weaving.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heddle-eye</ent>⟦br⟧
